modules.description: This module processes interval-based data using a generator to retrieve and fold over intervals and associated values. It works with `Interval.t` and lists of values, enabling iteration through a sequence of intervals. Use it to efficiently traverse or accumulate results from interval data, such as merging overlapping intervals or computing aggregate values per interval.

This module defines bound types for interval endpoints—`Included`, `Excluded`, and `Unbounded`—and provides comparison and selection operations tailored for lower and upper bounds. It supports precise interval merging and ordering through `compare_lower`, `compare_upper`, `min_lower`, and `max_upper`. Use cases include implementing interval maps with inclusive/exclusive ranges and managing overlapping or adjacent intervals in scheduling or numerical range analysis.

This module represents intervals defined by lower and upper bounds and provides operations to create intervals, compare them, and compute overlaps. It works with intervals composed of `Bound.t` values, ensuring valid ordering upon creation. Concrete use cases include determining overlapping time ranges, sorting intervals for scheduling, and validating numeric range intersections.

Handles intervals with ordered endpoints, supporting operations like merging overlapping intervals and querying ranges. Works with comparable data types like integers or custom types that define an order. Useful for scheduling systems or time-series data analysis where interval overlaps must be resolved.
